info.name: Fiscal
info.description:
# Overview

------

{[app_name]} retrieves user-authorized account and transactional data from financial institutions and returns it to third-party solutions in an organized, highly usable format.

{[app_name]}’s API has an architectural style of a RESTful design pattern. It uses HTTP as its underlying protocol, where standard HTTP verbs and HTTP response codes are used. Communication travels via HTTPS to ensure a secure data exchange. Almost every response body is JSON encoded, unless stated on the endpoint description. Since RESTful services and JSON are highly popular and most major development languages include a form to interact with these technologies, it's quite easy to integrate with {[app_name]}'s API.

Start using our API ASAP with just a few steps.

1. Register

   In order to gain entry to {[app_name]}, you need to register for a {[app_name]} account. If you haven’t already done so, please head over to our [website]({[app_url]}), sign up, accept our terms, and you’re good to go!

2. Play in the Sandbox

   Once you're registered, you'll be taken to the {[app_name]} Control Panel where you can obtain your sandbox key to start testing the API without the need for valid user credentials.

3. Access the Production Environment

   When you're ready to work with live data, you'll need to accept the {[app_name]} Service Agreement and upload the by-laws or your (or your client's) entity to validate the authenticity of those entering into the agreement with {[app_name]}.

4. 14-day Trial

   Want to give {[app_name]} a test drive before committing? Try us risk-free for up to 14 days.

5. Select a Plan

   At the end of the trial or any point prior, simply choose the plan that fits your needs and enjoy continuous feeds of financial data right at your fingertips.

# Authentication

------

{[app_name]} API has two types of authentication:

#### API KEY

```bash
curl URL \
-H "Authorization: api_key api_key={API_KEY}" \
-H MEDIA_TYPE \
-X METHOD \
-d PARAMS 
```

#### Bearer Token

```bash
curl URL \
-H "Authorization: Bearer {TOKEN}" \
-H MEDIA_TYPE \
-X METHOD \
-d PARAMS 
```

Type of Authentication required is defined by Resource

| Resource     | Auth Type      |
| ------------ | -------------- |
| Users        | `API KEY`      |
| Sessions     | `API KEY`      |
| Catalogs     | `Bearer Token` |
| Credentials  | `Bearer Token` |
| Accounts     | `Bearer Token` |
| Transactions | `Bearer Token` |
| Attachments  | `Bearer Token` |
| Documents  | `Bearer Token` |

# Environments

------

## Sandbox

Go from zero to hero with our sandbox sites. Ready to use while you integrate the Syncfy API services. They are fully loaded with Acme data that mimics real-world use cases, so you can test out all the use cases, API endpoints, use the widget, and implement webhooks.

We strongly recommend you to start your integration with the Sandbox environment. Go to production is as easy as changing your Sandbox API Key to Production API Key.

### ACME SAT

| id_site | Name | RFC | Password(CIEC) |
| ------------ | -------------- | -------------- | -------------- |
| 5da784f1f9de2a06483abec1 | CIEC (Sandbox) | ACM010101ABC CACX7605101P8 MISC491214B86 XAMA620210DQ5 FUNK671228PH6 EKU9003173C9 JES900109Q90 H&E951128469 IXS7607092R5 | test |
| 5f2c2aacd74b837fc10602c1 | CIEC Retenciones (Sandbox) | ​IIA040805DZ4 | test |

### ACME AFIP

| id_site | Name | CUIT | CUIT Contribuyente | Password(Clave) |
| ------------ | -------------- | -------------- | -------------- | -------------- |
|5f6b3aa990d9411ed6109d42 | AFIP Alta usuario (V1) | 30710946147 | 2041664000 | myPassword |


## Production

- `mx` SAT
- `ar` AFIP

See the full list on the [coverage page]({[app_url]}/coverage).

# Request

------

#### Structure

```bash
curl URL \
-H AUTH \
-H MEDIA_TYPE \
-X METHOD \
-d PARAMS
```

# Error Codes

------

Table of Error Codes defined in {[app_name]} API

| Code | Message               |
| ---- | --------------------- |
| 400  | Bad Request           |
| 401  | Unauthorized          |
| 402  | Payment Required      |
| 403  | Forbidden             |
| 404  | Not Found             |
| 429  | Too Many Requests     |
| 500  | Internal Server Error |
| 503  | Service Unavailable   |

# Rate limit

------

There are two types of rate-limit:

#### Rate limit by server

5 request per second 

#### Limit by credential

1 pull request per day

item.description:
Catalogues are collections of endpoints that are relevant to the data segmentation on some of the other endpoints.

#### List of Catalogues: 

1. Account Types
2. Attachment Types
3. Countries
4. Currencies
5. Sites Organization Types
6. Sites Organizations
7. Sites



#### Account Type

```json
{
    "id_account_type": "520d3aa93b8e778e0d000002",
    // {[app_name]} ID; The ID of the Acount Type assignated by {[app_name]}
    "name": "Credit Card"
    // String; The name of the Account Type
}
```

#### Attachment Type

{
    "id_attachment_type": "56bcdfca784806d1378b4567",
    // {[app_name]} ID; The ID of the Attachment Type assignated by {[app_name]}

}

item.description:
Credentials are the third-party data that is needed in order to authenticate with a third-party site. Credentials are encrypted upon arrival and won’t be available on any endpoint. Data pull from this endpoint is only complementary.

```json
{
    "id_credential": "5e73bfe6d036f64a591d8822", // ID of the credential. It will be found in the Accounts and Transactions that have been downloaded from the site where you authenticated.
    "id_user": "5dde750d8c91e77a123e7013", // ID of the user to which it belongs.
    "id_environment": "574894bf7848066d138b4570", //
    "id_external": "", // ID external
    "id_site": "5da784f1f9de2a06483abec1", // ID of the site
    "id_site_organization": "56cf4ff5784806152c8b4567", // Site organization ID.
    "id_site_organization_type": "56cf4f5b784806cf028b4569", // ID of the site organization type.
    "id_organization": "56cf4ff5784806152c8b4567", // ID of organization
    "is_authorized": 1, // Status flag, indicates if the credential is authorized.
    "is_locked": 0, // Status flag, indicates if the credential was detected as locked.
    "is_twofa": 0, // Status flag, indicates if the credential requires a 2fa method to enter the site.
    "can_sync": 0, // Status flag, indicates if a credential can be synchronized on demand without sending the values.
    "ready_in": 85894, // Time in milliseconds until the credential is able to sync on demand
    "username": "A**********C", // Obfuscated registered user name.
    "code": 200, // Synchronization result code (see codes section)
    "keywords": [ // Array with keywords obtained when processing the attachments of the Transactions, applies only to SAT invoices.
        "001",
        "002",
        "003",
        "3.3",
        "emitidas",
        "i",
        "impuestos",
        "recibidas",
        "retenciones",
        "timbrefiscaldigital",
        "traslados",
        "vigente"
    ],
    "dt_authorized": 1584644110, // Date of last authorization
    "dt_execute": 1584644070, // Date of the last time the credential was synced, either manually or by a {[app_name]} process.
    "dt_ready": 1584730510, //
    "dt_refresh": 1584644110 // Date of last time credential transactions were added or modified
}
```
